A Seattle Parks facilities maintenance compound is located in the northwest portion of this zone.
A dozen or more Lawson cypress trees in this zone, mostly adjacent to crew headquarters, show signs of root disease (flagging patches on foliage).
Removals due to presumed Phytophthora lateralis have occurred in the recent past, but without confirming lab culture.
